New Structure:
1. DatabaseConnection.java - Handles all database operations

connect(boolean useLocal) - Connects to MySQL (local or Docker)
disconnect() - Closes connection
executeAndDisplay(String sql) - Executes queries and prints formatted results
Includes retry logic and proper error handling

2. ReportManager.java - Updated main coordinator

Now accepts a DatabaseConnection object
generateAllReports() executes all 32 reports in a loop against the database
Displays progress with report numbers and descriptions
Includes a nice menu system for user selection

3. App.java - Backward-compatible entry point

Maintains your original structure
Can be run as the main class
Creates DatabaseConnection and ReportManager instances